  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment [W-AR-05 adversarial sample]",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. NOTE: This package contains adversarial weakener W-AR-05 (comparator absence or mismatch). One validation result intentionally omits the comparedAgainst link; a second validation result references a comparator dataset collected under cyclic fatigue loading conditions rather than the quasi-static compression-bending protocol mandated by the declared COU, constituting an undercutting inference-method mismatch (D3).",
