      "name": "Primary QoI comparison — stiffness and yield force (comparator link absent)",
      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness (N/mm) and yield force (N) were evaluated against bench-test measurements from eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested quasi-statically per ASTM F1717. The normalized error metric E/uval was computed for each QoI; all values fell below the pre-specified threshold of 1.96. The experimental dataset used as the reference standard is described in the associated study documentation and is identified by laboratory accession numbers LAB-A-2019-0041 and LAB-B-2019-0117. The comparator is considered appropriate for the declared COU because it represents the same device geometry, loading mode, and boundary conditions. No formal comparedAgainst linkage is recorded in this result object.",
      "passedAcceptanceCriteria": true,
      "metric": "E/uval",
      "metricValue": 1.43,
      "acceptanceThreshold": 1.96
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cyclic-fatigue-comparator-mismatch",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Secondary QoI comparison — force at 40 mm displacement (comparator-COU mismatch)",
      "description": "FEA-predicted force at 40 mm axial displacement was compared against a reference dataset collected under sinusoidal cyclic fatigue loading at 5 Hz (R = 0.1, 10^6 cycles, per ISO 12189), rather than the quasi-static monotonic ramp protocol specified by ASTM F1717 and required by the declared COU. The cyclic fatigue dataset (Comparator DS-FATIGUE-2020) was selected because it was the only multi-laboratory dataset available at the time of assessment with matching device geometry. The mean peak force from the fatigue protocol was used as a surrogate for the quasi-static 40 mm displacement force. Although the numerical agreement appears acceptable (predicted 1 847 N vs. comparator mean 1 902 N, ~2.9% difference), the inference method is fundamentally mismatched: cyclic fatigue loading produces progressive stiffness degradation and ratcheting displacement that are absent in quasi-static compression-bending. The comparator is therefore inappropriate for the declared COU, undercutting the validity of the agreement metric.",
      "passedAcceptanceCriteria": true,
      "metric": "percentDifference",
      "metricValue": 2.9,
