    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment yields an Accepted decision. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is acknowledged and risk-accepted given the prescriptive single-condition nature of ASTM F1717 and established regulatory precedent. Primary QoI comparisons (stiffness and yield force) are well-supported by the quasi-static bench test dataset. The force-at-40mm comparator mismatch (cyclic fatigue dataset used in place of quasi-static reference) is noted as a gap; however, the 2.9% numerical agreement and the availability of supporting quasi-static data from the primary comparison are judged sufficient to sustain the Accepted outcome at Medium assurance level. Residual uncertainty is within the declared model risk level 3 tolerance.",
